about.summary: Computes polychoric and polyserial correlations by quick "two-step" methods or ML, optionally with standard errors; tetrachoric and biserial correlations are special cases.

name: r-polycor
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.7-10' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-polycor
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/polycor_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/polycor/polycor_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: caea3beca2c889e12e5b976c20c19cf5a76d42e6329e9ab646112eeae8fcfc73

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
    - r-mvtnorm
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
    - r-mvtnorm

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('polycor')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('polycor')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://r-forge.r-project.org/projects/polycor/, https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=polycor
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Computes polychoric and polyserial correlations by quick "two-step" methods or ML,
    optionally with standard errors; tetrachoric and biserial correlations are special
    cases.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - jacodela
